---
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---
<footer class="relative mt-24 pt-16 pb-10 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-white/70 border-t-2 border-[var(--color-blue)]/15">
  {/* Drifting clouds */}
  <svg class="cloud" style="left: 4%; top: -30px; width: 160px;" viewBox="0 0 200 80" aria-hidden="true">
    <ellipse cx="60" cy="50" rx="55" ry="28" fill="#ffffff"/>
    <ellipse cx="110" cy="40" rx="48" ry="32" fill="#ffffff"/>
    <ellipse cx="150" cy="55" rx="40" ry="22" fill="#ffffff"/>
  </svg>
  <svg class="cloud" style="right: 8%; top: 20px; width: 120px; opacity: 0.7;" viewBox="0 0 200 80" aria-hidden="true">
    <ellipse cx="60" cy="50" rx="55" ry="28" fill="#ffffff"/>
    <ellipse cx="110" cy="40" rx="48" ry="32" fill="#ffffff"/>
    <ellipse cx="150" cy="55" rx="40" ry="22" fill="#ffffff"/>
  </svg>

  <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3 text-sm">
    <div>
      <p class="display text-2xl">
        <span class="text-[var(--color-orange)]">dude</span><span class="text-[var(--color-blue)]">wheresmylikeness</span><span class="text-[var(--color-blue)]/60">.com</span>
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] max-w-md">
        Mapping AI likeness rights. Built by
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-etzioni/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] no-underline hover:underline decoration-[var(--color-ink-soft)] underline-offset-2"
        >Daniel Etzioni</a>, drawing on AI likeness research
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="font-sans font-extrabold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs text-[var(--color-orange-deep)]">
        Not legal advice
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] max-w-md">
        This site is a starting reference, not legal advice. State law in this area is
        changing quickly; per-state pages show their last-verified date. Federal claims
        (Lanham Act false endorsement, defamation, NCII statutes) are available in every
        jurisdiction regardless of category.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="md:text-right">
      <p class="font-sans font-extrabold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs text-[var(--color-orange-deep)]">
        Small print
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] max-w-xs md:ml-auto text-xs">
        Visual direction affectionately pastiches the <em>Dude, Where's My Car?</em> (2000)
        movie poster. No affiliation with the film or its rights-holders. The bit on this
        site is the point.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[var(--color-muted)]">&copy; {year}</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>
